Lets Put This Together

Technical details	
Submit file	./src/main/java/*.java, pom.xml or build.gradle, README.md, etc.
Building a Microservice-based Application with Spring Cloud
Objective
Develop a microservice-based application that utilizes multiple external APIs for a comprehensive service. The application will leverage Netflix Eureka for service discovery and Netflix Zuul for API gateway functionality.

Project Overview
The application will simulate a travel booking system, allowing users to search for flights, hotels, and car rentals through various external APIs. It will consist of multiple microservices, each responsible for a specific functionality, and will be designed to communicate seamlessly using Spring Cloud features.

Requirements
1. Project Structure
Organize your project into the following microservices:

travel-booking/
|-- discovery-service/
|-- api-gateway/
|-- flight-service/
|-- hotel-service/
|-- car-rental-service/
|-- pom.xml
2. Microservices Implementations
A. Discovery Service
Service: Uses Netflix Eureka for service discovery.

Example DiscoveryServiceApplication.java

@SpringBootApplication
@EnableEurekaServer
public class DiscoveryServiceApplication {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(DiscoveryServiceApplication.class, args);
    }
}
B. API Gateway
Service: Uses Netflix Zuul as an API gateway to route requests to the appropriate services.

Example ApiGatewayApplication.java

@SpringBootApplication
@EnableZuulProxy
public class ApiGatewayApplication {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(ApiGatewayApplication.class, args);
    }
}
C. Flight Service
Service: Integrates with an external flight API (e.g., Skyscanner or Amadeus) to search for flights.

Example FlightServiceApplication.java

@SpringBootApplication
@EnableEurekaClient
public class FlightServiceApplication {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(FlightServiceApplication.class, args);
    }
}
Example FlightController.java

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/flights")
public class FlightController {
    
    @GetMapping("/search")
    public ResponseEntity<List<Flight>> searchFlights(@RequestParam String origin, @RequestParam String destination) {
    }
}
D. Hotel Service
Service: Integrates with an external hotel booking API (e.g., Booking.com or Hotels.com) to search for hotels.

Example HotelServiceApplication.java

@SpringBootApplication
@EnableEurekaClient
public class HotelServiceApplication {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(HotelServiceApplication.class, args);
    }
}
Example HotelController.java

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/hotels")
public class HotelController {
    
    @GetMapping("/search")
    public ResponseEntity<List<Hotel>> searchHotels(@RequestParam String location) {
    }
}
E. Car Rental Service
Service: Integrates with an external car rental API (e.g., Rentalcars.com or Enterprise) to search for cars.

Example CarRentalServiceApplication.java

@SpringBootApplication
@EnableEurekaClient
public class CarRentalServiceApplication {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(CarRentalServiceApplication.class, args);
    }
}
Example CarRentalController.java

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/cars")
public class CarRentalController {
    
    @GetMapping("/search")
    public ResponseEntity<List<Car>> searchCars(@RequestParam String location) {
    }
}
3. External API Integration
Use libraries like RestTemplate or WebClient to call the external APIs from each service.
Create service classes to encapsulate the API calls and handle responses.
4. Running the Application
Set up Eureka Discovery Server: Run the discovery service.

Run API Gateway: Run the API Gateway.

Run Microservices: Run the flight, hotel, and car rental services.

Testing: Use Postman or a similar tool to test the API Gateway endpoints.

5. Example API Gateway Endpoint
Get Flights: GET http://localhost:8080/flights/search?origin=NYC&destination=LAX

Get Hotels: GET http://localhost:8080/hotels/search?location=LosAngeles

Get Cars: GET http://localhost:8080/cars/search?location=LosAngeles

